> If you've ever wondered how to get your tofu as crisp and golden brown as the
> restaurants do, now's your chance—it's all about the drying and the dredging!

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @mini cucumber{1}. Thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating
whites from greens. Cut @broccoli florets{8%oz} into bite-size pieces if
necessary.

In a #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp},
@sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Mix thoroughly and set aside to pickle
until ready to serve.

== Scallion-Sesame Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp} in a #small pot{} (medium pot for 4
servings) over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring,
until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups} (2¼ cups for 4),
@sesame oil{1/2%tbsp} (all for 4), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then
cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Tofu ==

While rice cooks, open and drain @tofu{1}(pressed); press out excess water with
#paper towels{}. Halve crosswise, then stand tofu upright and halve
vertically. Lay flat and cut into ¾-inch cubes.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tofu, @cornstarch{1/2%tbsp}, and a big pinch of
salt. Stir until tofu is fully coated.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over
medium-high heat. Add coated tofu and cook, turning occasionally, until
browned on all sides, ~{4-6%minutes}. Reserve bowl.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

== Broccoli & Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for tofu over medium-high heat. Add broccoli
and a pinch of salt; cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

While broccoli cooks, in bowl used for tofu, whisk together @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp},
@sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, @sriracha{1%tsp}, @cornstarch{1/2%tbsp}, and
@water{1/3%cup} (2⁄3 cup for 4 servings).

Reduce heat under pan with broccoli to low and stir in hoisin-soy mixture.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is thickened and sticky, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Transfer seared tofu to pan. Stir until fully coated and tofu is warmed through,
~{1%minute}. Taste and season with @salt and @pepper if desired.

== To Serve ==

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with tofu and broccoli and pickled cucumber
(draining first) in separate sections. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.